722390f-a.title: Manhattan: Park Avenue - 106th Street
722390f-a.text:
Park Ave, north from but not including 106th Street, showing the
New York Central and Hudson River Railroad.
October 11, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.

722389f.title: Manhattan: Park Avenue - 106th Street
722389f.text:
Park Avenue, at the S. W. corner of E. 106th Street. The latter thoroughfare is on the right and the photographer is viewing westward towards Central Park (west side of 5th Avenue). The archway through which he is viewing is a part of the stone causeway
carrying the New York Central Railroad's tracks.
1938-9
Alexander Alland
This photo is one of a series that appeared in the published volume "Portratt of N. Y." by Felix Reisenberg and Alex. Alland, IRGV.
